race.comment: The local ZIPITALIST (7) spoiled things with a slow start here last time beaten 2.5L. Came from the back again and impressed prior beaten 1.5L in an 80 at Moruya. Peaks and his best form stacks right up. Finally draws an inside gate and should prove hard to beat. TIGER TOWN (6) was unwanted in betting first up but performed beyond expectations, beaten a head over 1250m at Newcastle. He's further improved and fitter is a decent chance to go one better. APOLLO MISSION (1) returned from a spell two weeks ago beaten 2L here over 1200m at this track and there was plenty of merit in the effort after settling rearward. Has won 2/4 second-up and has the inside gate today. Keeps the handy 2kg claim. Is still well shy of his best. PRETTY SASSY (9) has no luck in the same race beaten 1.6L and has more to give. Has a wide gate to manage but can't be ruled out.
